A POLICEMAN has been rushed to hospital after being stabbed while attending a disturbance this afternoon.
The officer suffered injuries to his leg during the incident in Hutton Drive, in Glasgow’s Govan area.
Police Scotland said the officer’s injuries were not life threatening.
A Police Scotland spokeswoman said: “Around 1.05pm, while attending an incident in the Govan area, a Police Scotland officer was injured.
“The officer has been taken to hospital for treatment and his injuries are not life threatening.
“Two men have been detained in connection with a disturbance in the area and inquiries are continuing to establish the exact circumstances.”
